title: Tate Jacobson
text:
I am an Assistant Professor in the Department of Statistics at Oregon State University. I completed my PhD in Statistics at the University of Minnesota where I worked with Professor Hui Zou. My research is mainly focused on developing new methods for analyzing high-dimensional data, though I am also interested in machine learning more broadly.





High-dimensional estimation and inference
Nonparametric and semi-parametric methods
Missing and censored data
Dimension reduction
Machine learning






PhD in Statistics, 2023
University of Minnesota, Minneapolis, MN
BA in Mathematics, 2016
Whitman College, Walla Walla, WA
